<description>
 <p>
   <b>SC4 part number:</b>  </p>
 <p>
   <b>(2) Clause:</b> ARM Express
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(3) Paragraph:</b> Observation_item
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(5) Comment:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
Observation_item identifies an item by its string-type identifier. The same id-string may be used in different context to identify different instances; an Observation_item may not identify an instance  unambiguously.
</p>
 <p>
   <b>(6) Proposal:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
Allow, at least in addition, the identification of an instance directly, by a pointer.
If this is not possible, Observation_item should get an additional attribute "identifier_role" that when being populated shall correspond to a Identification_assignment.role .</p>
 </description>

